dataIdInfo.idPurp: This data set was developed to be used as input to the Monarch Conservation Planning Tool - Milkweed Calculator (m2/ha). The attributes in fields attached to this shapefile denote the number of hectares of each habitat class.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: A seamless milkweed habitat raster was used as the source for the summary information contained within this shapefile. This raster data set was developed as part of the developement of the Monarch Conservation Planning Tools. There were a total of 42 different habitat classes created. These classes represent all areas on the landscape which may provide potential habitat for milkweed plants. This data set was created for the Conterminous lower 48 US States. This region is comprised of select U.S. counties. The geometry for this data set is taken from the 2015 TIGER U.S. Department of Commerce, U.S. Census Bureau, Geography Division counties data set. The values for each habitat class (i.e., cl001) represent the area of that class within that county in hectares.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: United States Department of Agriculture, Farm Service Agendy, National Land Cover Data Set, United States Geological Survey, U.S. Department of Commerce, U.S. Census Bureau, Geography Division, Homeland Security Infrastructure Program
